<title>PiJuice – unboxing, first look and why it’s 2 years late?</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2017/pijuice-unboxing-first-look-and-why-its-2-years-late</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2017/pijuice-unboxing-first-look-and-why-its-2-years-late</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-150x150.jpg&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;PiJuice unboxing first look and why so late?&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-300x300.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-768x768.jpg 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb-64x64.jpg 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/PiJuice-blog-thumb.jpg 1500w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’ve just received an early production PiJuice and two solar panels from Pi-Supply. It’s a loaner as there aren’t many of them in existence at the moment. In this video I take a first look at them and give my perspective on how/why it came to be so late.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;embed-youtube&quot;&gt;&lt;iframe class=&quot;youtube-player&quot; type=&quot;text/html&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;421&quot; src=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/oD049_9hAXU?version=3&amp;amp;rel=1&amp;amp;fs=1&amp;amp;autohide=2&amp;amp;showsearch=0&amp;amp;showinfo=1&amp;amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;amp;wmode=transparent&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;true&quot;&gt;[embedded content]&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DIP switch is to change the charge profile, not the i2c address as I said in the video.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It all looks very nice so far. I will start “playing” with it today. I’ve got this to play with for a few more days. I’ll publish another video with my findings some time next week.&lt;/p&gt;
