<title>New Raspberry Pi Family Photo 28 Feb 2017</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2017/new-raspberry-pi-family-photo-28-feb-2017</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2017/new-raspberry-pi-family-photo-28-feb-2017</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-150x150.jpg&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;Raspberry Pi Family Photo Feb 28th 2017&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-64x64.jpg 64w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This week the new Pi Zero W was launched. A few weeks ago the new compute Module 3 was launched. It’s the Pi birthday party tomorrow. This can only mean one thing. It’s time for a new Pi family photo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I had an interesting exchange with a publisher this week who wanted to use the November family photo in a book. They made me an offer. I added some terms. A contract was then sent to me, which absolutely didn’t reflect my terms and was very biased towards them. Under advice I declined it. So that’s not happening, but they were greedy. I was a bit rude, but it was last night after a fairly adrenaline-packed day (in case you don’t know, &lt;a href=&quot;http://rasp.io/inspiring&quot;&gt;I launched a KickStarter which funded in 8.63 hours WOOT!&lt;/a&gt;). No time for dealing with plonkers in that state. If you are a creator, DO NOT ACCEPT CRAP CONTRACTS FROM PUBLISHERS. TELL THEM TO GO SWING!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I make this photo available to the world at this resolution under &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/legalcode&quot;&gt;CC-BY-NC-SA4&lt;/a&gt; The only stipulation is that the RasPi.TV credit remains intact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So here’s the photo, and you can click it for a 1500px version.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_10081&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_1500.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Raspberry Pi Family Photo Feb 28th 2017&quot; width=&quot;700&quot; height=&quot;649&quot; class=&quot;size-full wp-image-10081&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700.jpg 700w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Pi-Family-Photo-Master-Feb2017_700-300x278.jpg 300w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
