<item>
<title>Pixel Tips and Tweaks – how to Tweak Aspects of the new Raspbian Skin</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2016/pixel-tips-and-tweaks-how-to-tweak-aspects-of-the-new-raspbian-skin</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2016/pixel-tips-and-tweaks-how-to-tweak-aspects-of-the-new-raspbian-skin</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-150x150.jpg&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;Pixel tips&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-300x300.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-768x768.jpg 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb-64x64.jpg 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Tweaking-pixel-thumb.jpg 1500w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last week. Simon Long from Raspberry Pi released a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.raspberrypi.org/blog/introducing-pixel/&quot;&gt;new version of Raspbian&lt;/a&gt; with several new features. The most visible of these is the new-look desktop skin, named PIXEL (Pi Improved Xwindows Environment, Lightweight).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9644&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pixel-splash_1500.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pixel-splash_1500-300x196.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PIXEL splash screen&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;196&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9644&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pixel-splash_1500-300x196.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pixel-splash_1500-768x501.jpg 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pixel-splash_1500-1024x668.jpg 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Pixel-splash_1500.jpg 1500w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PIXEL splash screen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s a lot of user interface (UI) tweaks both functional and visual…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;new splash screen on boot&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;stunning background images added&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;a whole new set of icons&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;larger ‘drag handles’ for resizing windows (that’s bugged me for years)&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;windows now have rounded corners&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;new font rendering package for better typography&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;I think the new look is a big improvement and I love it. ‘Grabbing’ the corner of a window to resize it has always been a bit harder than it should have been, so I’m delighted about the larger drag handles too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;So What Else is New?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other tweaks include using &lt;strong&gt;Chromium&lt;/strong&gt; as default browser and &lt;strong&gt;realvnc&lt;/strong&gt; is pre-installed. I’m delighted by the addition of Chromium as it means I can use a Pi3B for G+ hangouts which I use a lot &lt;em&gt;&lt;del datetime=&quot;2016-10-06T21:14:14+00:00&quot;&gt;when I should be working&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/em&gt; for communicating and collaborating with people. I can now do this in the workshop whilst monitoring twitter and QC testing &lt;a href=&quot;http://rasp.io/prohat&quot;&gt;Pro Hats&lt;/a&gt; – all using the same Pi3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;I Want to Tweak PIXEL&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But we all like to personalise our computing, so what if you want to tweak it for yourself? How would you manage that? Below are a few tips I’ve collected showing ways you can tweak or customise your PIXEL/Raspbian.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Don’t Want a Splash Screen?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you prefer the retro look of the boot messages racing by, rather than the splash screen, there are two ways to achieve this…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol readability=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;li readability=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Using raspi-config application, choose “boot to CLI” instead of “boot to desktop”&amp;#13;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9623&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config-300x295.png&quot; alt=&quot;Opening raspi-config&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;295&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9623&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config-300x295.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config-768x755.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config-24x24.png 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config-36x36.png 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config-48x48.png 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config-64x64.png 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspi-config.png 952w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Opening raspi-config&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9622&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/boot-to-CLI.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/boot-to-CLI-300x256.png&quot; alt=&quot;Select &amp;quot;To CLI&amp;quot;&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;256&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9622&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/boot-to-CLI-300x256.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/boot-to-CLI-768x656.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/boot-to-CLI.png 930w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Select “To CLI”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;If you boot to CLI (command line interface) and then want the desktop, you’ll need to type &lt;code&gt;startx&lt;/code&gt; to run it.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li readability=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Delete “quiet splash” from &lt;code&gt;/boot/cmdline.txt&lt;/code&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo nano /boot/cmdline.txt&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;#13;
remove &lt;code&gt;quiet splash&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9634&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-quiet-splash.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-quiet-splash-1024x188.png&quot; alt=&quot;Removing &amp;quot;quiet splash&amp;quot; disables splash screen&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;128&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9634&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-quiet-splash-1024x188.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-quiet-splash-300x55.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-quiet-splash-768x141.png 768w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Removing “quiet splash” disables splash screen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Save and exit (&lt;code&gt;CTRL+X, y, ENTER&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Want to Change the Splash Graphic?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is quite easy. All you have to do is replace &lt;code&gt;/usr/share/plymouth/themes/pix/splash.png&lt;/code&gt; with your chosen graphic. It must be called &lt;code&gt;splash.png&lt;/code&gt; though.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supposing your required splash graphic is &lt;code&gt;/home/pi/raspitv.png&lt;/code&gt; you would move (mv) it like this…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First let’s back up the old one in case we want to revert…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo cp /usr/share/plymouth/themes/pix/splash.png /usr/share/plymouth/themes/pix/oldsplash.png&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then move the new graphic…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo mv /home/pi/raspitv.png /usr/share/plymouth/themes/pix/splash.png&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt; is required because the target directory is owned by the &lt;code&gt;root&lt;/code&gt; user.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So then the default splash becomes your own customised version…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9643&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspitv-splash_1500.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspitv-splash_1500-300x194.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;RasPi.TV splash screen&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;194&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9643&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspitv-splash_1500-300x194.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspitv-splash_1500-768x497.jpg 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspitv-splash_1500-1024x662.jpg 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/raspitv-splash_1500.jpg 1500w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;RasPi.TV splash screen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE:&lt;/strong&gt; If you do a &lt;code&gt;dist-upgrade&lt;/code&gt; your splash file will be overwritten with the new official PIXEL one showing the new version.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;How to Disable Tooltips&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you hover over objects in the user interface, you see pop-out bubbles (‘callouts’) explaining what they are/do.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9631&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/tooltips-example.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/tooltips-example-300x160.png&quot; alt=&quot;Here's a tooltip (callout)&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9631&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/tooltips-example-300x160.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/tooltips-example-768x408.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/tooltips-example.png 974w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Here’s a tooltip (callout)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you no longer wish to see these, or find they get in your way, you can switch them off by adding a new line…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;gtk-enable-tooltips = 0&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;…right at the beginning of the file &lt;code&gt;~/.themes/PiX/gtk-2.0/gtkrc&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;nano ~/.themes/PiX/gtk-2.0/gtkrc&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;#13;
add&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;gtk-enable-tooltips = 0&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9625&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-tooltips.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-tooltips-300x177.png&quot; alt=&quot;Disable tooltips&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;177&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9625&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-tooltips-300x177.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-tooltips-768x452.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/remove-tooltips.png 948w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Disable tooltips&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then next time you restart LXDE the tooltips should be disabled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;I Miss the Raspberry Pi Desktop Logo. Can I Reinstate it?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes. You can select it with the Appearance Settings application – it lives here…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;/usr/share/raspberrypi-artwork/raspberry-pi-logo-small.png&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9627&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-300x297.png&quot; alt=&quot;Appearance settings&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;297&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9627&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-300x297.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-150x150.png 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-768x761.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-96x96.png 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-24x24.png 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-36x36.png 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-48x48.png 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings-64x64.png 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Appearance-Settings.png 938w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Appearance settings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9628&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Change-wallpaper.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Change-wallpaper-300x185.png&quot; alt=&quot;Selecting the Pi logo graphic&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;185&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9628&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Change-wallpaper-300x185.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Change-wallpaper-768x473.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Change-wallpaper.png 954w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Selecting the Pi logo graphic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then be sure to change “fill screen with image” to “centre image on screen” or the Pi logo will be huge.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9629&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Centre-image.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Centre-image-300x213.png&quot; alt=&quot;Centre image on screen&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;213&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9629&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Centre-image-300x213.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Centre-image-768x546.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Centre-image-1024x728.png 1024w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Centre image on screen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Where are the New Icons Stored?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All the new icons are here if you need access to them for your own documentation or apps…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;/usr/share/icons/PiX&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9639&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/icons.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/icons-1024x738.png&quot; alt=&quot;New icons' hiding place&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;501&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9639&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/icons-1024x738.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/icons-300x216.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/icons-768x554.png 768w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;New icons’ hiding place&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Enjoy Tweaking&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hopefully you found these ‘PIXEL tips’ useful. Enjoy tweaking your PIXELs. If you have any more tips, feel free to share them below in the comments.&lt;/p&gt;
