<item>
<title>Playing With Papirus Zero</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2016/playing-with-papirus-zero</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2016/playing-with-papirus-zero</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-150x150.jpg&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;PaPiRus Zero thumbnail&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-300x300.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-768x768.jpg 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail-64x64.jpg 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-thumbnail.jpg 1500w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A few weeks ago I did a &lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/2016/mailbag-july-2016-overview-of-papirus-zero-displayotron-hat-wombat-board-piot-relay-board-piups-motozero-zeroview&quot;&gt;“mailbag” video/blog&lt;/a&gt; and ran a poll on which product(s) you’d like me to review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There was a clear winner right from day one. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pi-supply.com/product/papirus-zero-epaper-screen-phat-pi-zero/&quot;&gt;Pi-Supply’s Papirus Zero&lt;/a&gt; took first place and held it by a comfortable margin for three weeks. So I’m going to have a play with that one first and share my findings with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9530&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_1500.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_700.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PapiRus Zero&quot; width=&quot;700&quot; height=&quot;329&quot; class=&quot;size-full wp-image-9530&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_700.jpg 700w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_700-300x141.jpg 300w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PapiRus Zero&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Initial Impressions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9534&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption alignright&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_1500.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-300x300.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Both PaPirus Zero Screens&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;300&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9534&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-300x300.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700-64x64.jpg 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-both_700.jpg 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Both PaPirus Zero Screens&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;It’s a nice dainty little display.&lt;/strong&gt; In my review pack there were two displays of different sizes; 1.44 inch and 2.0 inch. It just so happens that the height of these screens is an almost perfect match for the Pi Zero. The wider of the two doesn’t quite fill a pHAT sized board, so they both fit nicely on the PCB.
&lt;p&gt;The 1.44″ is 128 x 96&lt;br/&gt;&amp;#13;
The 2.00″ is 200 x 96&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both have a pixel density of 111 dpi with square pixels 0.229 x 0.229mm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They are very thin indeed. I got the calipers out and measured 0.95mm thickness of the TFT itself. The PCB and GPIO connector add significant “bulk”, but overall, the size is typical of a pHAT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It also has a built-in LM75 temperature sensor and 5 buttons connected to GPIO ports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Data Sheet Info&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;http://repaper.org/doc/eg020as012.html&quot;&gt;the data sheets&lt;/a&gt; they are… “active matrix TFT, Electronic Paper Display (EPD) panel. The panel has such high resolution (111 dpi) that it is able to easily display fine patterns. Due to its bi-stable nature, the EPD panel requires very little power to update and needs no power to maintain an image.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They also feature…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ultra low power consumption&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;Super Wide Viewing Angle – near 180°&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;Extra thin &amp;amp; light&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;SPI interface&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Hardware Setup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hardware setup is easy. You just connect the screen to the PCB using the ribbon cable and connector, then secure the other end with one of the supplied sticky pads, or using a little bit of tape (as I’ve done to enable swapping over the screens). Connecting the PCB to the Pi requires care to avoid putting pressure on the screen. It would be easy to crack the thin glass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Software Installation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first generation PaPirus was widely criticised for being hard to install and use. Is the Papirus Zero any better? I’m delighted to say that it was for me. I just followed the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/PiSupply/PaPiRus&quot;&gt;installation instructions on GitHub&lt;/a&gt; and was delighted to see that “it just worked”. I’m always a happy bunny when that happens – even though it ought to be ‘&lt;em&gt;normal&lt;/em&gt;‘.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Built-in Demos&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are several demo programs in the PaPirus software installation. Each one is run from the command line using &lt;code&gt;sudo xxx-yyy&lt;/code&gt;…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;papirus-clock&lt;/code&gt; Is a basic clock demo showing time and date. It updates once every five seconds from the Pi’s system time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9546&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-clock_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-clock_700-300x138.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PaPirus Zero clock demo&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;138&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9546&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-clock_700-300x138.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-clock_700.jpg 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PaPirus Zero clock demo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;papirus-gol&lt;/code&gt; runs Conway’s game of life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9548&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-GOL_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-GOL_700-300x145.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PaPirus Zero GoL demo&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;145&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9548&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-GOL_700-300x145.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-GOL_700.jpg 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PaPirus Zero GoL demo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;papirus-temp&lt;/code&gt; displays the temperature of the LM75 temperature sensor on the PCB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9547&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-temp_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-temp_700-300x144.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PaPirus Zero temperature demo&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;144&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9547&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-temp_700-300x144.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-temp_700.jpg 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PaPirus Zero temperature demo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;papirus-buttons&lt;/code&gt; press one of the five onboard buttons and it will show which button you pressed on the screen. (This worked partially for me. Not all of the buttons ‘did something’ and the order was not quite as expected.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9545&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-buttons_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-buttons_700-300x145.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PaPirus Zero buttons demo&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;145&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9545&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-buttons_700-300x145.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Papirus-buttons_700.jpg 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PaPirus Zero buttons demo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, these last three examples didn’t work at all for me…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;papirus-snakes&lt;/code&gt; A snakes game&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;papirus-system&lt;/code&gt; Show system information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;papirus-framepush&lt;/code&gt; Push framebuffer to screen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What Else Can You Do With It?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are Python and command line interfaces for controlling the PaPirus Zero screen output. You can display text or images limited only by your imagination and the the shape, size and monochromatic nature of the screen. You must run the scripts as root to be able to control the screen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To write text to the screen…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;brush: python; title: ; notranslate&quot; title=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#13;
from papirus import PapirusText&amp;#13;
text = PapirusText()&amp;#13;
text.write(&quot;PaPirus Zero Review by RasPi.TV&quot;)&amp;#13;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or from the command line…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo papirus-write &quot;PaPirus Zero Review by RasPi.TV&quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9549&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-text_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-text_700-300x142.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PaPirus Zero Text demo&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;142&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9549&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-text_700-300x142.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-text_700.jpg 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PaPirus Zero Text demo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To display an image on the screen…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;brush: python; title: ; notranslate&quot; title=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#13;
from papirus import PapirusImage&amp;#13;
image = PapirusImage()&amp;#13;
image.write('/home/pi/PaPiRus/RasPiO-logo-200.jpg')&amp;#13;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or from the command line…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo papirus-draw /home/pi/PaPiRus/RasPiO-logo-200.jpg&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9530&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_700-300x141.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;PaPirus Zero&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;141&quot; class=&quot;size-medium wp-image-9530&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_700-300x141.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/PapiRus_Zero-front_700.jpg 700w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;PaPirus Zero&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the RasPiO image there are a few “stray pixels” that do not appear in the original graphic file, which was resized to fit the screen perfectly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Strengths And Weaknesses&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PaPirus Zero…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;is awesome for applications requiring infrequent refresh and low power usage&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;has an excellent viewing angle&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;is fine for relatively low res graphics as long as they work in monochrome&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;is not good at applications needing fast screen refresh (by which I mean more often than once every few seconds).&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;could do with some nicer/alternative fonts on the text interface&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;is easier to install and use than previous editions. The software is much better, but some of the examples don’t work (for me).&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Where and How Much?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can get a PaPirus Zero from &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pi-supply.com/product/papirus-zero-epaper-screen-phat-pi-zero/&quot;&gt;Pi-Supply&lt;/a&gt; priced at…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;£24 for the smaller screen&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;£26 for the larger screen&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;£40 for both screens&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Vine&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here’s a little ‘Vine’ showing you some of what it can do…&lt;/p&gt;

