<title>RasPiO GPIO Zero Ruler</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2016/raspio-gpio-zero-ruler</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2016/raspio-gpio-zero-ruler</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-150x150.jpg&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-300x300.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-768x768.jpg 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000-64x64.jpg 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/GPIO-Zero-ruler-KS-graphic-thumbnail_1000.jpg 1000w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may remember this time last year I KickStarted a 6-inch ruler with the most important &lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/rpi-gpio&quot;&gt;RPi.GPIO&lt;/a&gt; code on it. I’ve been using it myself an awful lot in the last year when coding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So it won’t surprise you to learn that I’m now doing another one for &lt;a href=&quot;http://rasp.io/gpiozeroruler&quot;&gt;GPIO Zero&lt;/a&gt;. Since GPIO Zero is about the easiest way imaginable to get into Python GPIO tinkering, I think this will be really helpful for people. I’ve already been using the prototypes and find them an extremely helpful reference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Here’s what it looks like…&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;7&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://rasp.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/front-and-back-cleaned-cutout-1500.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://rasp.io/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/front-and-back-cleaned-cutout-1500.png&quot; width=&quot;1500&quot; height=&quot;247&quot; alt=&quot;RasPiO GPIO Zero Ruler&quot; class=&quot;&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;RasPiO GPIO Zero Ruler (click to enlarge)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s twice as long as the previous one. It’s now 12 inches (30cm) because there is quite a lot to fit in.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/raspitv/raspio-gpio-zero-code-reference-ruler-for-raspberr/&quot;&gt;Come And Have a Look&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/raspitv/raspio-gpio-zero-code-reference-ruler-for-raspberr/&quot;&gt;It has already reached funding target in a little over 4 hours, so will definitely be happening.&lt;br/&gt;&amp;#13;
Please come along and back RasPiO GPIO Zero Ruler.&lt;/a&gt; Shipping will start in September/October 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
