<title>Raspberry Pi Zero 1.3 Power Usage with camera</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2016/raspberry-pi-zero-1-3-power-usage-with-camera</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2016/raspberry-pi-zero-1-3-power-usage-with-camera</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-150x150.png&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;Raspberry Pi Power usage chart updated for Pi Zero 1.3&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-150x150.png 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-96x96.png 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-24x24.png 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-36x36.png 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-48x48.png 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-64x64.png 64w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s only a few days since the Pi Zero 1.3 came out, but people are already asking for me to “fill in the gap” on my power chart. Which gap? The “Pi Zero shooting 1080p video” gap. With no camera port, the previous Pi Zero couldn’t do this, so there was no measurement to report. I’ve made some measurements this morning and here are the results…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9422&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-table.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-table-1024x276.png&quot; alt=&quot;Raspberry Pi Power usage table&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;187&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9422&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-table-1024x276.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-table-300x81.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-table-768x207.png 768w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Raspberry Pi Power usage table&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9423&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-1024x544.png&quot; alt=&quot;Raspberry Pi Power usage chart updated for Pi Zero 1.3&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;369&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9423&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-1024x544.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-300x160.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-Power-Usage-Chart-768x408.png 768w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Raspberry Pi Power usage chart updated for Pi Zero 1.3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;No Real Surprises&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I tried both old and new cameras and there wasn’t any significant difference (that I could measure) between them. The results are comparable to that of the A+, which is hardly surprising. Even though slightly higher, I’d call it the same within experimental error.&lt;/p&gt;
