<item>
<title>Raspberry Pi Zero 1.3 with camera port</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2016/raspberry-pi-zero-1-3-with-camera-port</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2016/raspberry-pi-zero-1-3-with-camera-port</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-150x150.jpg&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;Pi Zero with camera port&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-300x300.jpg 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-768x768.jpg 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000-64x64.jpg 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3-thumb_1000.jpg 1000w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A new Raspberry Pi Zero with camera port is released today. It’s revision 1.3. Some power circuitry was moved and some unpopulated pads at U13 were removed to make space for the new mini camera port which is right on the end of the Pi Zero 1.3. Other than that, the new Zero looks much the same as the previous version. I did a little walkaround video, showing use of the camera port and camera output.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;embed-youtube&quot;&gt;&lt;iframe class=&quot;youtube-player&quot; type=&quot;text/html&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;421&quot; src=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/kpoqxVJ_X2Y?version=3&amp;amp;rel=1&amp;amp;fs=1&amp;amp;autohide=2&amp;amp;showsearch=0&amp;amp;showinfo=1&amp;amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;amp;wmode=transparent&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;true&quot;&gt;[embedded content]&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9408&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-top_1500.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-top_700.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Pi Zero 1.3 with camera port&quot; width=&quot;700&quot; height=&quot;277&quot; class=&quot;size-full wp-image-9408&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-top_700.jpg 700w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-top_700-300x119.jpg 300w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Pi Zero 1.3 with camera port&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9407&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-bottom_1500.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-bottom_700.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Pi Zero 1.3 with camera port (underside)&quot; width=&quot;702&quot; height=&quot;280&quot; class=&quot;size-full wp-image-9407&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-bottom_700.jpg 702w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Pi-Zero-1.3-bottom_700-300x120.jpg 300w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Pi Zero 1.3 with camera port (underside)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adding a camera port to the Zero has opened up a whole new range of project possibilities. It’s added a lot of value to the Zero without adding a lot of cost. That’s a big win, in my view. Hearty congrats to Raspberry Pi and nice work Mike Stimson. :)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9412&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3_700.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Pi Zero 1.3 showing camera connected&quot; width=&quot;700&quot; height=&quot;424&quot; class=&quot;size-full wp-image-9412&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3_700.jpg 700w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/PiZero1.3_700-300x182.jpg 300w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Pi Zero 1.3 showing camera connected&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
