<title>How To Free Up Some Space On Your Raspbian SD Card? Remove Wolfram &amp; LibreOffice</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2016/how-to-free-up-some-space-on-your-raspbian-sd-card-remove-wolfram-libreoffice</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2016/how-to-free-up-some-space-on-your-raspbian-sd-card-remove-wolfram-libreoffice</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-150x150.png&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-150x150.png 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-300x300.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-768x768.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-1024x1024.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-96x96.png 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-24x24.png 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-36x36.png 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-48x48.png 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space-64x64.png 64w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Freeing-Up-SD-card-space.png 1298w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are occasions when you may want to free up some space on your (micro)-SD card. If it’s getting full, or you want to store large media files, or install a large application, you may find you run out of space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s an awful lot of good stuff in the default Raspbian Jessie distro these days, but you may not be using all of it on all of your Pis. So, let’s have a look at which of the pre-installed packages take up a lot of space and could give us “an easy win” here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you don’t want a full desktop, there is Jessie Lite too (under a Gigabyte) but, if you want a leaner card with a desktop pre-installed removing, some large packages may be a better way to go.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Which Are The Easy Wins?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you don’t need them, these applications take up a lot of space…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wolfram (658 MB)&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;libreoffice (253 MB)&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;…and some of their dependencies take up space too. Clearing them both and using &lt;code&gt;clean&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;autoremove&lt;/code&gt; freed up over a Gigabyte of space on my micro-SD card.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let me show you what I mean. Typing &lt;code&gt;df -h&lt;/code&gt; shows you your disk usage. If you look at the first entry &lt;code&gt;/dev/root/&lt;/code&gt; it shows 3.9G used and 3.0G available…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9309&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-doing-anything.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-doing-anything-1024x435.png&quot; alt=&quot;Before doing anything&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;295&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9309&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-doing-anything-1024x435.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-doing-anything-300x128.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-doing-anything-768x327.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/before-doing-anything.png 1298w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Before doing anything&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then I typed…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo apt-get purge wolfram-engine&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;…which showed me I could free up 658 MB, so I did it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9310&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/removing-wolfram.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/removing-wolfram-1024x436.png&quot; alt=&quot;Removing Wolfram&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;296&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9310&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/removing-wolfram-1024x436.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/removing-wolfram-300x128.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/removing-wolfram-768x327.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/removing-wolfram.png 1540w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Removing Wolfram&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I then checked how much space was freed up…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9311&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-wolfram.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-wolfram-1024x436.png&quot; alt=&quot;After Wolfram removal&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;296&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9311&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-wolfram-1024x436.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-wolfram-300x128.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-wolfram-768x327.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-wolfram.png 1288w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;After Wolfram removal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then I ran these two commands…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo apt-get clean&lt;br/&gt;&amp;#13;
sudo apt-get autoremove&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9312&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wolfram-autoremove.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wolfram-autoremove-1024x364.png&quot; alt=&quot;After Wolfram autoremove&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;247&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9312&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wolfram-autoremove-1024x364.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wolfram-autoremove-300x107.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wolfram-autoremove-768x273.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wolfram-autoremove.png 1526w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;After Wolfram autoremove&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then I did the same with libreoffice…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo apt-get remove --purge libreoffice*&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;…which showed another large space saving of 253MB…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9313&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-remove.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-remove-1024x288.png&quot; alt=&quot;libreoffice remove&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;195&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9313&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-remove-1024x288.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-remove-300x84.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-remove-768x216.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-remove.png 1564w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;libreoffice remove&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo apt-get clean&lt;br/&gt;&amp;#13;
sudo apt-get autoremove&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9314&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-autoremove.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-autoremove-1024x547.png&quot; alt=&quot;libreoffice autoremove&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;371&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9314&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-autoremove-1024x547.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-autoremove-300x160.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-autoremove-768x410.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/libreoffice-autoremove.png 1524w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;libreoffice autoremove&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And then I checked the disk space again. OK, the numbers don’t quite add up. I’m not sure why, but it looks as if I now have 1.3GB more micro-SD card space than I had before…&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9315&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-all-of-it.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-all-of-it-1024x435.png&quot; alt=&quot;Disk usage after removing both&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;295&quot; class=&quot;size-large wp-image-9315&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-all-of-it-1024x435.png 1024w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-all-of-it-300x128.png 300w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-all-of-it-768x326.png 768w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/after-all-of-it.png 1280w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Disk usage after removing both&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So after removing these two bulky packages and cleaning up, it looks like we’ve redeemed 1.3 GB of SD card space. That was a relatively easy win and didn’t take very long.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Those are the “low-hanging fruit” (raspberries of course) if you need an extra Gigabyte of space on your Raspbian SD card. I don’t recommend you bother doing this unless you need to though.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There may be other large packages you don’t use. If you have other suggestions, leave a comment.&lt;/p&gt;
