<title>New 8 Megapixel Raspberry Pi camera 2.1 launches</title>
<link>http://raspi.tv/2016/new-8-megapixel-raspberry-pi-camera-2-1-launches</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://raspi.tv/2016/new-8-megapixel-raspberry-pi-camera-2-1-launches</guid>
<description>&lt;div class=&quot;left-thumbnail&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;150&quot; src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_1500-150x150.jpg&quot; class=&quot;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image&quot; alt=&quot;Raspberry Pi camera 2.1 and NOIR 2.1&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_1500-150x150.jpg 150w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_1500-96x96.jpg 96w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_1500-24x24.jpg 24w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_1500-36x36.jpg 36w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_1500-48x48.jpg 48w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_1500-64x64.jpg 64w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The new 8 Megapixel Raspberry Pi camera is released today. It’s fully backward compatible with all camera-enabled Raspberry Pis produced to-date. It uses a SONY IMX219 sensor capable of 3280 x 2464 pixel stills. It’s mechanically almost identical to the previous camera model (V1.3) except for rounded corners on the PCB – and there’s no red LED on the front. There’s also a NOIR version being released at the same time. They both support 1080p30, 720p60 and 640x480p90 video.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here’s a video overview…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;embed-youtube&quot;&gt;&lt;iframe class=&quot;youtube-player&quot; type=&quot;text/html&quot; width=&quot;695&quot; height=&quot;421&quot; src=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/W8SdTZRVjPw?version=3&amp;amp;rel=1&amp;amp;fs=1&amp;amp;autohide=2&amp;amp;showsearch=0&amp;amp;showinfo=1&amp;amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;amp;wmode=transparent&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;true&quot;&gt;[embedded content]&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_9302&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption aligncenter&quot; readability=&quot;32&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_700.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_700.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Raspberry Pi camera 2.1 and NOIR 2.1&quot; width=&quot;700&quot; height=&quot;380&quot; class=&quot;size-full wp-image-9302&quot; srcset=&quot;http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_700.jpg 700w, http://raspi.tv/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Picameras2_700-300x163.jpg 300w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;wp-caption-text&quot;&gt;Raspberry Pi camera 2.1 and NOIR 2.1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Specifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lens:&lt;/strong&gt; Fixed focus&lt;br/&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Megapixels:&lt;/strong&gt; 8 megapixel native resolution sensor&lt;br/&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Camera Resolution:&lt;/strong&gt; 3280 x 2464 pixel stills&lt;br/&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Video Resolution:&lt;/strong&gt; 1080p30, 720p60 and 640x480p90 video&lt;br/&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dimensions:&lt;/strong&gt; 25mm x 23mm x 9mm&lt;br/&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weight:&lt;/strong&gt; ~3g&lt;br/&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Connector:&lt;/strong&gt; ribbon connector&lt;br/&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interface:&lt;/strong&gt; CSI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Where Can I Get One?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://thepihut.com/collections/raspberry-pi-camera&quot;&gt;The Pi Hut&lt;/a&gt;, RS, Farnell and all good Pi retailers.
